{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017720,"pPcc":"SAT#H","questionId":"9b886541","skill_cd":"H.A.","score_band_range_cd":3,"skill_desc":"Linear equations in one variable","createDate":1755117017720,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Algebra","ibn":"","external_id":"8076db82-ac6c-4ac2-a6b7-46a9a4b4059b","primary_class_cd":"H","uId":"118e0308-fa7b-4d05-9af0-94ba845a1b66","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If <math alttext=\"3 x minus 8 equals 7\"><mrow>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mn>3</mn>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>-</mo>\n\t\t<mn>8</mn>\n\t</mrow>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mn>7</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>, what is the value of <math alttext=\"3 x plus 8\"><mrow>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mn>3</mn>\n\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t</mrow>\n\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t<mn>8</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>?</span></p>","keys":["e80968e7-9cde-4ed1-aa26-c2fe52516c0b"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"67cd1793-b2cb-45e1-abfb-e977ee772801","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><math alttext=\"negative 1\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>"},{"id":"10fbb038-b7ae-4e37-ba59-d089c4f3febe","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><math alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn>\n</math></span></p>"},{"id":"fd5d12b1-6639-49d8-b152-1898ce16266f","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><math alttext=\"13\"><mn>13</mn>\n</math></span></p>"},{"id":"e80968e7-9cde-4ed1-aa26-c2fe52516c0b","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><math alttext=\"23\"><mn>23</mn>\n</math></span></p>"}],"rationale":"<p>Choice D is correct. It's given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 x minus 8 equals 7\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>. Adding&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> to both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 x equals 15\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math>. Adding <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> to both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 x plus 8 equals 23\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>23</mn></math>. Therefore, the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 x plus 8\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"23\"><mn>23</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect. This is the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 x plus 8\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>","externalid":"8076db82-ac6c-4ac2-a6b7-46a9a4b4059b","correct_answer":["D"]}}